# Cursor Workspace Rules – Starboard AI Agent

> Full project context is in `CLAUDE.md`. Detailed engineering standards are in `.cursor/01-08*.md`.
> These rules govern **Cursor-specific behavior only** to avoid duplicating those files.

---

## Change Management

- Make the smallest, safest change that satisfies the request.
- Do not restructure the project (move/rename files or folders) unless explicitly asked.
- Write change docs, summaries, hand-offs, architecture and design specs to the `changes/` folder.
- Propose minimal diffs; preserve public APIs unless a spec change requires otherwise.
- Never insert secrets directly; use environment variables and document them in `examples/env.example`.

## When Adding New Code

- Add or adjust tests in the appropriate `tests/` directory.
- Use typed, documented functions (type hints + Google-style docstrings).
- Wire observability (structured logging with trace_id, span_id) and token/cost tracking where relevant.
- Use Pydantic models or TypedDicts for AI input/output validation.
- Prefer async implementations; never block the event loop with sync I/O.

